    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="51"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914, midnight</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>We have received no request from German Embassy. If request is made we shall of
                    course accede to it but with the understanding that it will not prevent our
                    acting for other nations in case they also request. We still hope most sincerely
                    that a general war may be averted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
